Contrarywiſe, that we make them not altogether ſo carnall and vngoſtly, that it myghte he thought, howe that naturall and fraile bodies ſhall be in the glory. Olde wryters ſay alſo, that Origen did not perfectly confeſſe the reſurrection of ye fleſhe,Origen. but that in the reſurrection he fantaſied and imagined ſuche a body, as hathe little difference


from a ſprite. And therefore in Definicionibus Ecleſiaſticis,
                  Definici. Eccle. ca. 6 there is a Chapter againſte the ſaide Origen, in maner folowing.
